notes.name: Course Note
notes.content:
Timetable Instructions
This is an online hybrid course. Lectures will be mainly asynchronous, but there will be the occasional request for students to be online at the given times. It is strongly preferred that students have access to a webcam. Restricted to students enrolled in the International Foundation Program. For more information, please contact foundation.program@utoronto.ca or 416-946-5146.
Classes will be mainly asynchronous, but there may be the occasional request for students to be online at the given times. While not required, it is strongly preferred that students have access to a webcam.

cmCourseInfo.description: Surveys the development of human societies from their origins to the present.  Topics may include the environment, cultural development and interaction, the creation and nature of belief systems, political, economic and social structures, gender relations, and the relationship between global patterns and local development. Restricted to students enrolled in the summer offering of the International Foundation Program (IFP). Not eligible for CR/NCR option.
cmCourseInfo.title: Themes in World History
